data.text:
Dean's List

The University awards semester academic honors (Dean's List) to undergraduate students who complete, within any given semester (excluding winter and summer terms), 12 or more credits (excluding courses with grades of P and S) with a semester GPA of 3.500 or higher. This recognition is noted on the student's academic record. The Robert H. Smith School of Business is proud to announce for the Spring 2024 semester that the following Smith School students were awarded semester academic honors.
